cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the coverage and spectral efficiency of cellular networks using device-to-device relays. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of stochastic geometry to derive expressions for coverage probability and spectral efficiency. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with millimeter-wave propagation and its limitations. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a system-level solution to improve the performance of millimeter-wave cellular networks. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on social or ethical issues related to technology.
